'''Tagajinja''' (多賀神社) is a {{ill|Shinto Shrine|ja|神社}} located in {{ill|Ehime Prefecture|ja|愛媛県}}, {{ill|Matsuyama City|ja|松山市}}, {{ill|Shinritsu-cho|ja|新立町}}. The divine emblem is {{ill|Left Mitsudomoe|ja|左三つ巴}}.

== Deities ==
* {{ill|Izanagi|ja|イザナギ|lt=Izanagi-no-Mikoto|lt_ja=いざなぎのみこと}}
* {{ill|Izanami|ja|イザナミ|lt=Izanami-no-Mikoto|lt_ja=いざなみのみこと}}

== History ==
* In Kan'ei 5 ({{ill|1628|ja|1628}}), when {{ill|Gamo Tadayoshi|ja|蒲生忠知}} became the lord of {{ill|Iyo Matsuyama Domain|ja|伊予松山藩|lt=Matsuyama Domain|lt_ja=松山藩}}, he enshrined his family's tutelary deity, {{ill|Taga Taisha|ja|多賀大社}} (Taga, Shiga Prefecture).
* In Taishō 2 ({{ill|1913|ja|1913}}), {{ill|Shokonsha|ja|招魂社}} was relocated to the shrine grounds for the construction of the {{ill|Ehime Prefectural Agricultural School|ja|愛媛県立農業学校}}.
* In Shōwa 14 (1939), in April, {{ill|Shokonsha|ja|招魂社}} was designated by the Minister of Home Affairs as {{ill|Ehime Prefectural Gokoku Shrine|ja|愛媛縣護國神社}}, and on October 9 of the same year, it was relocated to its current location (Miyuki-cho, Matsuyama City).

== Annual Events ==
{| class="wikitable"
! Date !! Festival
|-
| January 1 || {{ill|New Year's Festival|ja|歳旦祭}} &nbsp;
|-
| June 30 || {{ill|Great Purification|ja|大祓|lt=Summer Purification Festival|lt_ja=夏越祭}} &nbsp;
|-
| August 3-4 || Summer Grand Festival (Lamp Offering Festival) &nbsp;
|-
| October 6 || {{ill|Festival|ja|festival|lt=Autumn Grand Festival|lt_ja=秋季大祭}} &nbsp;
|-
| October 7 || {{ill|Shinkosai|ja|神幸祭}} &nbsp;
|-
| November 15 || {{ill|Shichi-Go-San|ja|七五三}} &nbsp;
|}

== Other ==
* It holds a dedication plaque in the autograph of the haiku poet {{ill|Masaoka Shiki|ja|正岡子規}}.
* It houses the {{ill|Yata no Kagami|ja|八咫鏡|lt=Eight-Foot Mirror|lt_ja=八呎の鏡}} associated with the white snake legend.
* It possesses one of the largest taiko drums in the Kansai region, and the largest in Ehime Prefecture (Enju Taiko). This drum was crafted from the root portion of one of two sacred trees from the former Onsen District, Haishi Village, with the other located at {{ill|Ōyamazumi Shrine|ja|大山祇神社}} (Ōmishima-cho, Imabari City).
* For a period, {{ill|Shokonsha|ja|招魂社}} (later known as {{ill|Ehime Prefectural Gokoku Shrine|ja|愛媛縣護國神社}}) was enshrined here.

== Access ==
* A 2‑minute walk from {{ill|Iyo Tetsu Bus|ja|伊予鉄バス}} Shinritsu Bus Stop

== Nearby Facilities ==
* {{ill|Kotohira Shrine Matsuyama Branch|ja|金刀比羅宮松山分社}}
* {{ill|Ehime Prefectural Matsuyama Commercial High School|ja|愛媛県立松山商業高等学校}}
* {{ill|Matsuyama Municipal Yatsuzaka Elementary School|ja|松山市立八坂小学校}}
* {{ill|Matsuyama Municipal Soga Elementary School|ja|松山市立素鵞小学校}}
* Sakura Kindergarten (attached to the shrine grounds)

== See Also ==
* {{ill|Yasukuni Shrine|ja|靖国神社}}
* {{ill|Ehime Prefectural Gokoku Shrine|ja|愛媛縣護國神社}}

{{citation neededたかしんしや}}

