== Other ==
* It holds a dedication plaque in the autograph of the haiku poet {{ill|Masaoka Shiki|ja|正岡子規|12=draft|12=draft}}.
* It houses the {{ill|Yata no Kagami|ja|八咫鏡|lt=Eight-Foot Mirror|lt_ja=八呎の鏡|12=draft|12=draft}} associated with the white snake legend.
* It possesses one of the largest taiko drums in the Kansai region, and the largest in Ehime Prefecture (Enju Taiko). This drum was crafted from the root portion of one of two sacred trees from the former Onsen District, Haishi Village, with the other located at {{ill|Ōyamazumi Shrine|ja|大山祇神社|1=Ōyamazumi Shrine|12=draft|12=draft}} (Ōmishima-cho, Imabari City).
* For a period, {{ill|Shokonsha|ja|招魂社|12=draft|12=draft}} (later known as {{ill|Ehime Prefectural Gokoku Shrine|ja|愛媛縣護國神社|12=draft|12=draft}}) was enshrined here.

