'''Tagajinja''' (多賀神社) is a {{ill|Shinto Shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} located in {{ill|Ehime Prefecture|ja|愛媛県|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Matsuyama City|ja|松山市|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, {{ill|Shinritsu-cho|ja|新立町|qq=draft|qq=draft}}. The divine emblem is {{ill|Left Mitsudomoe|ja|左三つ巴|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.

== Deities ==
* {{ill|Izanagi|ja|イザナギ|lt=Izanagi-no-Mikoto|lt_ja=いざなぎのみこと|qq=draft|qq=draft}}
* {{ill|Izanami|ja|イザナミ|lt=Izanami-no-Mikoto|lt_ja=いざなみのみこと|qq=draft|qq=draft}}

== History ==
* In Kan'ei 5 ({{ill|1628|ja|1628|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), when {{ill|Gamo Tadayoshi|ja|蒲生忠知|qq=draft|qq=draft}} became the lord of {{ill|Iyo Matsuyama Domain|ja|伊予松山藩|lt=Matsuyama Domain|lt_ja=松山藩|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, he enshrined his family's tutelary deity, {{ill|Taga Taisha|ja|多賀大社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} (Taga, Shiga Prefecture).
* In Taishō 2 ({{ill|1913|ja|1913|qq=draft|qq=draft}}), {{ill|Shokonsha|ja|招魂社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} was relocated to the shrine grounds for the construction of the {{ill|Ehime Prefectural Agricultural School|ja|愛媛県立農業学校|qq=draft|qq=draft}}.
* In Shōwa 14 (1939), in April, {{ill|Shokonsha|ja|招魂社|qq=draft|qq=draft}} was designated by the Minister of Home Affairs as {{ill|Ehime Prefectural Gokoku Shrine|ja|愛媛縣護國神社|qq=draft|qq=draft}}, and on October 9 of the same year, it was relocated to its current location (Miyuki-cho, Matsuyama City).

