'''Tagajinja''' (多賀神社) is a {{ill|Shinto Shrine|ja|神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinto Shrine|qq=}} located in {{ill|Ehime Prefecture|ja|愛媛県|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ehime Prefecture|qq=}}, {{ill|Matsuyama City|ja|松山市|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Matsuyama City|qq=}}, {{ill|Shinritsu-cho|ja|新立町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinritsu-cho|qq=}}. The divine emblem is {{ill|Left Mitsudomoe|ja|左三つ巴|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Left Mitsudomoe|qq=}}.

== Deities ==
* {{ill|Izanagi|ja|イザナギ|lt=Izanagi-no-Mikoto|lt_ja=いざなぎのみこと|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izanagi|qq=}}
* {{ill|Izanami|ja|イザナミ|lt=Izanami-no-Mikoto|lt_ja=いざなみのみこと|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Izanami|qq=}}

== History ==
* In Kan'ei 5 ({{ill|1628|ja|1628|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1628|qq=}}), when {{ill|Gamo Tadayoshi|ja|蒲生忠知|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gamo Tadayoshi|qq=}} became the lord of {{ill|Iyo Matsuyama Domain|ja|伊予松山藩|lt=Matsuyama Domain|lt_ja=松山藩|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Iyo Matsuyama Domain|qq=}}, he enshrined his family's tutelary deity, {{ill|Taga-taisha|lt=Taga-taisha|lt=Taga Taisha|ja|多賀大社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Taga Taisha|qq=}} (Taga, Shiga Prefecture).
* In Taishō 2 ({{ill|1913|ja|1913|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/1913|qq=}}), {{ill|Gokoku Shrines|lt=Gokoku Shrines|lt=Shokonsha|ja|招魂社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shokonsha|qq=}} was relocated to the shrine grounds for the construction of the {{ill|Ehime Prefectural Agricultural School|ja|愛媛県立農業学校|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ehime Prefectural Agricultural School|qq=}}.
* In Shōwa 14 (1939), in April, {{ill|Gokoku Shrines|lt=Gokoku Shrines|lt=Shokonsha|ja|招魂社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shokonsha|qq=}} was designated by the Minister of Home Affairs as {{ill|Ehime Prefectural Gokoku Shrine|ja|愛媛縣護國神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ehime Prefectural Gokoku Shrine|qq=}}, and on October 9 of the same year, it was relocated to its current location (Miyuki-cho, Matsuyama City).

