'''Tagajinja''' (多賀神社) is a [[:en:Shinto shrine|Shinto Shrine]] located in [[:en:Ehime Prefecture|Ehime Prefecture]], [[:en:Matsuyama|Matsuyama City]], {{ill|Shinritsu-cho|ja|新立町|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shinritsu-cho|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}. The divine emblem is {{ill|Left Mitsudomoe|ja|左三つ巴|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Left Mitsudomoe|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki redirects to 巴|1=tomoe|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q1557435}}.

== Deities ==
* [[:en:Izanagi|Izanagi-no-Mikoto]]
* [[:en:Izanami|Izanami-no-Mikoto]]

== History ==
* In Kan'ei 5 ([[:en:1628|1628]]), when {{ill|Gamo Tadayoshi|ja|蒲生忠知|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Gamo Tadayoshi|qq=|1=Gamō Tadatomo|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q8513824}} became the lord of [[:en:Iyo-Matsuyama Domain|Matsuyama Domain]], he enshrined his family's tutelary deity, [[:en:Taga-taisha|Taga Taisha]] (Taga, Shiga Prefecture).
* In Taishō 2 ([[:en:1913|1913]]), {{ill|Gokoku Shrines|lt=Gokoku Shrines|lt=Shokonsha|ja|招魂社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shokonsha|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} was relocated to the shrine grounds for the construction of the {{ill|Ehime Prefectural Agricultural School|ja|愛媛県立農業学校|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ehime Prefectural Agricultural School|qq=|ja_comment=jawiki link invalid}}.
* In Shōwa 14 (1939), in April, {{ill|Gokoku Shrines|lt=Gokoku Shrines|lt=Shokonsha|ja|招魂社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Shokonsha|qq=|comment=enwiki is a redirect}} was designated by the Minister of Home Affairs as {{ill|Ehime Prefectural Gokoku Shrine|ja|愛媛縣護國神社|qq=draft|qq=draft|12=simple|13=User:Immanuelle/Ehime Prefectural Gokoku Shrine|qq=|1=Ehime Gokoku Shrine|comment=changed title based on wikidata|WD=Q11493796}}, and on October 9 of the same year, it was relocated to its current location (Miyuki-cho, Matsuyama City).

